    "summary": "Roef is a passionate professional in Manufacturing & SCM with more than 25 years\u2019 experience in blue chip FMCG & Pharma companies and an excellent track record of delivering both short- & long-term results. \n\nBuilding on many years of practical experience in manufacturing, procurement, S&OP and logistics, he deeply understands how to lead complex international supply chains.  Experience includes growth & investment, restructuring, cost leadership, operational excellence and new construction. Also, he has a broad experience with developing and implementing supply chain & manufacturing strategies, as well as with mergers & acquisitions. \n\nRoef has worked for listed multinationals, a cooperative, mid-size private equity and start-up/scale-ups. In B2B and B2C environments, in cost leadership, customer-intimacy and growth-innovation models.  Experience stretches beyond hardcore Ops into HRM, industrial relations, organizational transformation, ERP-implementations and non-executive board roles.  He has been based in the Netherlands, Moscow, Warsaw and Munich, leading operations across Europe, Russia and South Africa.\n\nRoef is a highly energetic leader, combining a sharp analytical mind with a strong solution-orientation. A  team player, with a deep interest in people & organization, and the capability to build and mobilize strong teams. He will set high standards for himself and others and is focused on delivering meaningful results in a sustainable way.  His motto: Let\u2019s make it better. Together.\n\nIn the various way\u2019s Roef can contribute to your organization; \n- COO/Head of Operations (interim or permanent).\n- Project-based roles for 6-12 months. Supply chain strategy, M&A/DD, turn-arounds, continuous improvement.\n- Wing man for CEO/COO during a transformation or a restructuring process.\n- Coaching of individuals, support of (operational) leadership teams.\n- Advisory roles.  Supply chain strategy & implementation, organizational development , capability building.\n- Non-executive board roles.",
